stimulusHtml: Respond to all parts of the question.

features.html:
In answering the question, you should emphasize the line of reasoning that generated your results; it is not enough to list the results of your analysis. Include correctly labeled diagrams, if useful or required, in explaining your answers. A correctly labeled diagram must have all axes and curves clearly labeled and must show directional changes.

Indicate whether each of the following is counted in the United States gross domestic product for the year 2006. Explain each of your answers.

  1. The value of a used textbook sold through an online auction in 2006

  2. Rent paid in 2006 by residents in an apartment building built in 2000

  3. Commissions earned in 2006 by a stockbroker

  4. The value of automobiles produced in 2006 entirely in South Korea by a firm fully owned by United States citizens
